body:
@bzz @jongyoul This push _should_ have removed the extraneous git artifacts.  It is still a lot of files.  If we want to split it up into smaller bits, I suggest that we make the documentation and the tests separate PRs.  That's a natural way to break it up.  

Note: This is intended to address @bzz's issues 1-3.  It does not yet address issues 5-7  That's tomorrow.

Oh - this also pulls-out the demo notebook.  That was never intended as part of the PR, and was only there to help people review it.  If you want to test the PR and see what it does, I suggest grabbing the notebook out of my repo.
